<h2 class="pageTitle"><span>Computer Science Student Opportunities -new</span></h2>

</div>
<div class="contentMain">


<div id="pageContent"><h4>Do you find this web page useful? Did you find dead links? Send feedback to Sue Jandro at <a href="mailto:sjandro@carleton.edu">sjandro@carleton.edu</a>.</h4>
<h3><a name="corporate" id="corporate"></a>Corporate Full-time Jobs and Summer Internships</h3>
<p><a name="corporate" id="corporate"></a></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="//apps.carleton.edu/curricular/cs/news/">Carleton Sentinel</a> always has the latest information regarding who is on campus hiring. <a href="https://lists.carleton.edu/info/carleton_sentinel">Subscribe to the Sentinel</a> to get updates by email.</li>
<li>Carleton alumni are a fantastic resource for finding job opportunities. Deb Olien of the Carleton Career Center provides <a href="http://www.cs.carleton.edu/faculty/dmusican/alumninetworking.doc">these tips on how to network with alumni</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.epic.com/">Epic Systems</a> in Madison, WI recruits on campus regularly, and has hired a number of Carleton grads. We received an email recently stating they are very impressed with the quality of our students.&nbsp;</li>
<li>EdLab, a research, design and development unit at <a target="_blank" href="http://edlab.tc.columbia.edu/">Teachers College</a>, Columbia University, is looking for programmers. If interested, email <a target="_blank" href="mailto:edlabjobs@gmail.com">Pollyanna Rhee</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bungeelabs.com/">Bungee Labs</a> sent us a flyer indicating that they are looking for summer interns and full-time employees. Visit <a target="_blank" href="http://www.bungeeconnect.com/about/careers.html">their recruiting page</a> for more information.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.digitalcyclone.com/">Digital Cyclone</a> in Minnetonka, MN has contacted us regularly indicating interest in hiring Carleton students. Visit <a href="http://www.digitalcyclone.com/careers.jsp">their employment page</a> for current hiring information.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.netspi.com/">NetSPI</a> is a computer security company in Minneapolis that has hired a number of Carleton graduates in the past. Visit their <a target="_blank" href="http://www.netspi.com/company/careers.php">career page</a> for current hiring information.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.securecomputing.com/">Secure Computing</a> is a computer security company in Minneapolis that has hired a considerable number of computer science majors from Carleton. Visit <a href="http://www.securecomputing.com/index.cfm?skey=13">their employment page</a> for current hiring information. Also consider contacting directly <a href="mailto:Dave_Diehl@securecomputing.com">Dave Diehl</a>, who is a Carleton grad in a management position there.</li>
<li>Google has regularly come to campus indicating that they are interested in hiring full-time people and interns. Visit <a href="http://www.google.com/support/jobs/bin/static.py?page=about.html">Google's job page</a> for current hiring information.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.corporateinterns.com/">Corporate Interns</a> regularly advertises entry-level positions for Twin Cities companies. They have contacted us about a number of computing jobs.</li>
<li>Fog Creek Software in New York City is <a href="http://www.fogcreek.com/Jobs/SummerIntern.html">looking for summer interns</a>. They pay $750 per week, and that includes free housing, weekday lunches, round-trip airfare, and weekly cultural activities.</li>
<li>Carleton alum Alex Feinberg at <a href="http://www.care2.com/">Care2</a> tells us that they are looking for web developers to work in the Bay Area. Check out <a href="http://www.care2.com/aboutus/careers.html">the Care2 recruiting site</a> for more info. Alex says that they are interested as well in people that don't necessarily pigeonhole into the technical positions on the recruiting site, and you should <a href="mailto:alex.feinberg@gmail.com">email Alex</a> if you would like more information.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.prescio.com/home.asp">Prescio Consulting</a> tells us that they're looking to hire new computer science grads. Check out their web site for more information.</li>
<li>Carleton alum <a href="mailto:cmschmidt@mitre.org">Charles Schmidt '97</a> in the Crypto and IA Research department at the MITRE Corp. has openings for a summer intern an a number of full time workers. <a href="mailto:cmschmidt@mitre.org">Email him directly</a> for more info.</li>
<li>Carleton alum Nat Beagley '94 is looking for interns for the <a href="http://www.pnl.gov/Statistics">Pacific Northwest National Laboratory (PNNL) Statistical Sciences Group</a>. Check out their <a href="http://science-ed.pnl.gov/undergrad/fellowships.stm">internship web page</a> for more info.</li>
<li>Target Corporation, with headquarters in Minneapolis, is <a href="http://target.com/careers">hiring new graduates</a> for their Technology Leadership Program.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.intel.com/jobs/usa/students/">Intel</a> is hiring for both summer internships and full-time jobs.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.acm.org/membership/career/careerline.html">Association for Computing Machinery Careers Page</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www-01.ibm.com/employment/us/extremeblue/">IBM's Extreme Blue summer internship program</a>.</li>
<li>ZS Associates, a sales and marketing company that I used to work for, is hiring. According to Abhijit Nimgaonkar: "We are recruiting frantically now, so if anyone is interested in a consulting career, please direct them to <a href="http://www.zsassociates.com/">www.zsassociates.com</a>... CS is definitely one of our target disciplines."</li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.mobiata.com/">Mobiata</a> (founded by Carleton Computer Science graduate Ben Kazez '07) is looking for engineers who are interested in iPhone, Android, and BlackBerry! Check out their website for more information.</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="academic" id="academic"></a></p>
<h3><a name="academic" id="academic"></a>Academic and Research-Oriented Opportunities and Internships</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nsf.gov/crssprgm/reu/reu_search.cfm">REU Search Page</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.uwosh.edu/computer_science/reu-site-summer-2009">University of Wisconsin - Oshkosh REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://reu.cs.ua.edu/">University of Alabama REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://surf-it.soe.ucsc.edu/">UC Santa Cruz REU</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.depauw.edu/univ/reu/index.html">DePauw University REU</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.hci.iastate.edu/REU/">Iowa State University REU</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.nserc.und.edu/learning/SARP.html">The National Suborbital Education and Research Center</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://parasol.tamu.edu/dreu/">DREU: Distributed Research Experiences for Undergraduates</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.vcu.edu/csbc/bbsi/">Virginia Commonwealth University's Bioinformatics and Bioengineering Summer Institute</a></li>
<li><a href="http://arch.eece.maine.edu/superme">University of Maine REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ncat.edu/%7Emath/">North Carolina A&amp;T Summer Information Assurance Program</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.trinity.edu/%7Eyzhang/reu/reu.html">Trinity University REU</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://reu.cse.sc.edu/">University of South Carolina REU</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.cs.rit.edu/">Rochester Institute of Technology (RIT) REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://pages.csam.montclair.edu/%7Erobila/iMagine/">Montclair State University REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.hmc.edu/reu/">Harvey Mudd REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://hst.mit.edu/servlet/ControllerServlet?handler=PublicHandler&amp;action=browse&amp;pageid=2001">Harvard-MIT Health Sciences and Technology Summer Institute</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.orau.gov/dhsinternships/">Department of Homeland Security Summer Internships Program</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.cic.net/Home/Students/SROP/Introduction.aspx">Committee on Institutional Cooperation Summer Research Opportunities Program</a></li>
<li><a href="http://education.nasa.gov/usrp">NASA Undergraduate Student Research Program (NASA-USRP)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://dimacs.rutgers.edu/REU">REU at the Center for Discrete Mathematics and Theoretical Computer Science (DIMACS) at Rutgers University</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.jhu.edu/gifted/ctysummer">Summer Employment at Johns Hopkins University's Center for Talented Youth</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mcs.anl.gov/about/education.php">Undergraduate Program in Computational Science at Argonne National Laboratory</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ece.umn.edu/groups/nsfreu/">University of Minnesota Electrical and Computer Engineering REU</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.msi.umn.edu/programs/undergraduateinternship.html">University of Minnesota Supercomputing Institute Undergraduate Internship Program</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.hope.edu/reu">Hope College REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.virginia.edu/%7Eacw/REU/">University of Virginia REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cse.sc.edu/%7Eeastman/NSF-REU/">University of South Carolina REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://reu.owu.edu/">Ohio Wesleyan University REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://harvardforest.fas.harvard.edu/education/reu/reu.html">Harvard Forest REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.uncc.edu/reu">University of North Carolina Charlotte REU</a></li>
<li>The Council on Undergraduate Research has initiated a <a href="http://www.cur.org/ugreg">Registry of Undergraduate Researchers</a> (free of charge). The purpose of this registry is to facilitate matchmaking between undergraduates with research experience and a desire to pursue an advanced degree, and graduate schools seeking high quality students who are well prepared for research.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cra.org/Activities/craw/dmp/">Computing Research Association (CRA) Committee on the Status of Women in Computing Research (CRA-W) Distributed Mentor Project</a></li>
<li><a href="http://facweb.cs.depaul.edu/research/vc/medix/2007/index.htm">DePaul University and Northwestern University Medical Informatics REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://orise.orau.gov/doescholars">U.S. Department of Energy Scholars</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.teachforamerica.org/">Teach for America</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.src.wisc.edu/">Synchrotron Radiation Center (SRC) REU</a></li>
<li><a href="http://reu.cse.wustl.edu/">Washington University in St. Louis REU</a></li>
</ul>
